value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the spindle checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase/anaphase transition until the spindle is correctly assembled and oriented, and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

definition.value: Note that this term should not be used for direct manual annotation as it should always be possible to specify the type of checkpoint (i.e mitotic spindle or DNA damage etc).

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a muscle system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in a muscle system.

Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of mitochondrial fission. Mitochondrial fission is the division of a mitochondrion within a cell to form two or more separate mitochondrial compartments.

label.value: regulation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: positive regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: negative regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: positive regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: negative regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.

label.value: positive regulation of mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.

label.value: negative regulation of mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.

label.value: positive regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.

label.value: negative regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.
Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleic acids.

definition.value: This term should not be used for direct annotation. It should be possible to make a more specific annotation to one of the children of this term.

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle that contributes to the process of meiosis.

Mitotic bipolar spindle assembly begins with spindle microtubule nucleation from the separated spindle pole body, includes spindle elongation during prometaphase, and is complete when all kinetochores are stably attached the spindle, and the spindle assembly checkpoint is satisfied.

label.value: positive regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label.value: negative regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the phosphorylation of ADP to ATP that accompanies the oxidation of a metabolite through the operation of the respiratory chain. Oxidation of compounds establishes a proton gradient across the membrane, providing the energy for ATP synthesis.

label.value: regulation of locomotion involved in locomotory behavior

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another in a behavioral context; the aspect of locomotory behavior having to do with movement.

label.value: positive regulation of locomotion involved in locomotory behavior

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another in a behavioral context; the aspect of locomotory behavior having to do with movement.

label.value: negative regulation of locomotion involved in locomotory behavior

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of the self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another in a behavioral context; the aspect of locomotory behavior having to do with movement.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of DNA-templated DNA replication, the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of platelet aggregation. Platelet aggregation is the adhesion of one platelet to one or more other platelets via adhesion molecules.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of platelet aggregation. Platelet aggregation is the adhesion of one platelet to one or more other platelets via adhesion molecules.

label.value: regulation of brown fat cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of brown fat cell differentiation. Brown fat cell differentiation is the process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a brown adipocyte, an animal connective tissue cell involved in adaptive thermogenesis. Brown adipocytes contain multiple small droplets of triglycerides and a high number of mitochondria.

label.value: positive regulation of brown fat cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of brown fat cell differentiation. Brown fat cell differentiation is the process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a brown adipocyte, an animal connective tissue cell involved in adaptive thermogenesis. Brown adipocytes contain multiple small droplets of triglycerides and a high number of mitochondria.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving ornithine, an amino acid only rarely found in proteins, but which is important in living organisms as an intermediate in the reactions of the urea cycle and in arginine biosynthesis.
Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of cholesterol efflux. Cholesterol efflux is the directed movement of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3-beta-ol, out of a cell or organelle.

label.value: negative regulation of excitatory postsynaptic potential

value.value: Any process that prevents the establishment or decreases the extent of the excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP) which is a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell. The flow of ions that causes an EPSP is an excitatory postsynaptic current (EPSC) and makes it easier for the neuron to fire an action potential.
A cell aging process associated with the dismantling of a cell as a response to telomere shortening and/or cellular aging.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the biosynthesis of deoxyribose phosphate, the phosphorylated sugar 2-deoxy-erythro-pentose.

The epithelial cell differentiation process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an acinar cell, a secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape-shaped clusters known as acini.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location within a nuclear envelope.
The directed movement of glutamate into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of glutamate within a cell.
The directed movement of catecholamine into a cell.
The directed movement of dopamine into a cell.

label.value: mesenchyme migration involved in limb bud formation

value.value: The migration of mesenchymal tissue that contributes to the formation of a limb bud.
